 <text>
  <body>
   <p><figure type="seal"><ab>UNITED WE STAND, DIVIDED WE FALL.
<lb/>KENTUCKY.</ab></figure></p>
<p>Head-Quarters <orgName ref="cwgk:O00000870">Kentucky Volunteers</orgName>,
<lb/><orgName ref="cwgk:O00000388">ADJUTANT GENERAL'S OFFICE</orgName>,
<lb/><placeName ref="cwgk:P00000308">Frankfort</placeName>, <date when="1863-09-14">Sept<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> 14 1863</date>.
<lb/>Gen<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">l</hi></hi> <persName ref="cwgk:N00005245">L. Thomas</persName>.
<lb/>Adj<hi rend="sup">t</hi> Gen<hi rend="sup">l</hi> <orgName ref="cwgk:O00002945">U. S. A.</orgName>
<lb/><placeName ref="cwgk:P00001134">Washington. D. C.</placeName>
<lb/>Sir,</p>
<p>I have the honor to request that one First &amp; one second Lieutenant may be added to the <orgName ref="cwgk:O00011727">3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> Battery Kentucky Artillery</orgName> commanded by <persName ref="cwgk:N00013716">Capt. Neville</persName>. This Battery has just been recruited and was mustered into the <orgName ref="cwgk:O00001186">U. S. service</orgName> on the 11<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">"</hi></hi> instant </p>
<p>By General Order N<hi rend="sup">o</hi> 110 the above Officers may be added at <persName ref="cwgk:N001760">the President</persName>s discretion.</p>
<p>I trust that the additional Officers will be allowed this Battery.</p>
<p>By order of the <persName ref="cwgk:N001000">Governor</persName>
<lb/><persName ref="cwgk:N00000879">John Boyle</persName>
<lb/><hi rend="underline">Adj</hi><hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">t</hi></hi><hi rend="underline"> Gen</hi><hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">l </hi></hi><hi rend="underline">Ky Vols</hi><pb/></p>
<p>K.548. (V.S) ,<date when="1863">1863</date><figure type="hr"/></p>
<p>Frankfort.
<lb/><date when="1863-09-14">Sept. 14. 1863</date>.<figure type="hr"/></p>
<p><placeName ref="cwgk:P001800">Kentucky</placeName> -- State of<figure type="hr"/></p>
<p>John Boyle.
<lb/>Adj't. Genl.<figure type="hr"/></p>
<p>Requests that one 1<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">st</hi></hi> and 2<hi rend="sup">d</hi> Lt. may be added to the 3<hi rend="sup">d</hi> Btty Ky. Arty.<figure type="hr"/></p>
<p>Rec<hi rend="sup">d</hi> (A. G. O) <date when="1863-09-19">Sept. 19/63</date></p>
<p>{E. B. 232.V.5.}</p>
<p><orgName ref="cwgk:O00005118">War dept.</orgName> <orgName ref="cwgk:O00010608">A. G. O.</orgName>
<lb/><date when="1863-09-19">Septr 19. 1863</date></p>
<p>Respectfully returned </p>
<p>If the Battery has been recruited to the maximum, the additional Officers allow'd by G. O. 110 will be permitted.</p>
<p>By order of the <persName ref="cwgk:N00002647">Secretary of War</persName>
<lb/><persName ref="cwgk:N00005761">Thomas M Vincent</persName>
<lb/>Asst. Adjt. Genl</p>
